Before creating your first vinification you must configure the app once. This involves
the **Vinification Setup** page, the grape and wine **items**, and the wine treatment
**reason codes**.

## Vinification Setup

Search for **Vinification Setup** using *Tell Me* and fill in the fields below.

### Number series and location

| Field | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| **Vinification Nos.** | The number series used to assign a unique number to each new vinification document. |
| **Default Location Code** | The default warehouse/cellar location proposed on new vinification documents. |

### Reason codes

Each wine treatment phase is posted with a dedicated **reason code**. The reason codes
must be flagged as wine treatment reason codes (the *Wine Treatment* mark in the EOS WINE
reason code setup).

| Field | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| **Vinification Reason Code** | Reason code for the initial vinification treatment. |
| **Fermentation Reason Code** | Reason code for the fermentation treatment. |
| **Wine Production Reason Code** | Reason code for the wine production treatment. |
| **Cellar Surplus Reason Code** | Reason code for the cellar surplus produced beyond the standard yield. |
| **Coal Treatment Reason Code** | Reason code for the activated carbon (coal) treatment of grape must. |

### Units of measure and lot numbering

| Field | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| **KG Unit of Measure** | The unit of measure that represents kilograms, used for weight-based quantity conversions. |
| **Liter Unit of Measure** | The unit of measure that represents liters, used for volume-based quantity conversions. |
| **Use Last Lot No.** | When enabled, output items are pre-filled with the most recently used lot number where applicable. |